reviews.text:
Very delicious food and best place to go for the egg lovers! 
If you are not a big fan of egg, the pork chop is a very good alternate and it’s super yum!

The staffs are not very kind but it worths to try. I ordered with a picture on the wall because they don't have English menu. The combination of sweetened bun, salty eggs, butter cannot be bad. Would to try other foods too.
Delicious dishes, if you dont mind they serves the rice is cold

One of the best streetfood experience in HK. It is really local. The speciality here are asian menues with egg. The have the in house restaruant and on the other side of the street  another outdoor area. They speak english and help with choosing the food. Really nice.

short queue during lunch hour. had slight expectation on the food but nothing too "wow". the eggs were juicy and soft, yet chasiu were a bit thin and dry. the soy sauce was good with some spring onion in it.
招牌三寶飯，滑蛋叉燒飯，味道是不錯。不過還是沒有以前老板娘做的味道好吃！
我真心不會叫平時茶餐廳order到嘅A,B,C...餐，一定係食車仔面式嘅腸粉啦！
滑蛋飯好吃，只係個飯等得耐。
